01/07/2008
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- The first water shipment from Greece reached the drought-stricken island of Cyprus late Monday (June 30th). 
Officials said a tanker arrived on the southern coast of the island near Limassol shortly after midnight. 
Cypriot Agriculture Minister Andreas Polynikis says Greece has agreed to sell 8 million cubic meters of water by November 15th. 
(AFP, Reuters, ANA-MPA, Kathimerini, CAN, Philelefteros - 30/06/08)
